      </paragraph>
      <paragraph label="Proof">
       As discussed in Lemma 26, {a mathematical formula}K45n and {a mathematical formula}AXn are able to reduce any α to one in the provably equivalent NF[12]. That is, let α be a disjunction of formulas {a mathematical formula}αu that are of the form {a mathematical formula}σ∧ζ∧ξ:{a mathematical formula} where σ is a propositional formula, and {a mathematical formula}ϕi,φi are i-objective formulas. The proof is by an induction on t.For the base case, we consider {a mathematical formula}α∈OLn−. In [12, Theorem 5.5], it is proven that for {a mathematical formula}α∈OLn−, {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢α iff {a mathematical formula}AXn⊢α. It follows, then, α is consistent wrt {a mathematical formula}AXn iff α is consistent wrt {a mathematical formula}AXn′ iff {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(α)[12, Proposition 5.1]. So assume the theorem holds for {a mathematical formula}α∈OLnt−1.We prove the claim for {a mathematical formula}OLnt as follows:{a mathematical formula}
       <list>
        {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢⋁S(αu) by Proposition 43{a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(αu) for some u{a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(σ), {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(ζ) and {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(ξ) by Proposition 42.Observe that, because
       </list>
       <paragraph>
        σ is propositional, {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(σ) iff σ is consistent wrt {a mathematical formula}AXnt (by the base case). We now prove that {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(ζ) iff ζ is consistent wrt {a mathematical formula}AXnt. Essentially, as we have seen earlier in Theorem 37, consistency of ζ holds iff {a mathematical formula}ϕ0∧ϕz,z≥1 and {a mathematical formula}ψ0∧ψz′,z′≥1 are consistent wrt {a mathematical formula}AXnt while {a mathematical formula}¬ϕ0∧¬ψ0 is not {a mathematical formula}AXnt-consistent iff by induction (because {a mathematical formula}ϕi,ψi∈OLnt−1): {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢⋀S(ϕ0∧ϕz), {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢⋀S(ψ0∧ψz′) and {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢V(ϕ0∨ψ0), i.e.{a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(ζ) by V3. By symmetric arguments, we can show that {a mathematical formula}AXn′⊢S(ξ) iff ξ is consistent wrt {a mathematical formula}AXnt.Continuing from above, we then have:{a mathematical formula}
       </paragraph>
       <list>
        <list-item label="iff">
