    <section label="5">
     <section-title>
      Generalizing autoepistemic logic
     </section-title>
     <paragraph>
      Levesque related only knowing to the notion of stable sets and stable expansions, which are the basis for AEL [8]. Stable sets and expansions, in a certain sense, rationally reconstruct perfect introspection via meta-theoretic arguments. But besides the independent semantical account to nonmonotonicity in a monotonic framework, Levesque also generalizes Moore's account to a quantificational language with equality.
     </paragraph>
